##Dictation | today is the sixth day of Gao's quarantine

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Like Lao Gao, we are all waiting for this day. As an ordinary citizen working hard in Wuhan, I love this city and hope Wuhan will be better. I hope my story can bring you strength.

Dictation | Chen Xuan

Tidying up | bamboo

I'm Chen Xuan, 48, from Jiayu County, Xianning City, Hubei Province. In 2013, Lao Gao and I returned to our hometown in Hubei Province after 17 years of hard work in Zhongshan. I worked as a Baker in Wuhan. Lao Gao is in Jiayu County. We have a 23-year-old son, he is currently pursuing a master's degree at a university in Zhongshan. Family reunions are rare at the end of the year, and I had planned to drive with Gao to Zhongshan for the Spring Festival holiday this year, but things took a turn on January 21.

On the morning of January 20, news of the new type of coronary pneumonia began to appear on mobile phones. At that time, the citizens on Wuhan Street didn't seem to take it seriously. Few of them wore masks, but I was a little worried. Before Lao Gao came to Wuhan from Jiayu, I repeatedly told him: must wear a mask, must wear a mask. But as I expected, stubborn old high do not care, so "bald" to go home.

On the morning of the 21st we set off for Zhongshan, before the city was sealed off. Along the way, colleagues and friends texted me that they had all opted for home quarantine and urged us to wear masks and not run off when we arrived at Zhongshan. At this point we were already very defensive, wearing masks all the way, never took off, but at this time, the old high began to have a little low fever, body temperature around 37.2 degrees Celsius, I began to panic: What if infection?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A shop assistant wearing a mask at a supermarket in Wuhan

Gao reassured me that it was nothing. Maybe it was just a common cold. Despite what they say, we both wore extra N95 masks before we met our son. The son knew this situation, the first time sent us to the hospital, and took the initiative to tell the doctor said, we are from Hubei, to see whether to take measures. Fortunately, both the General Clinic and the fever clinic were given a temperature of 36.7, and the doctor advised home observation.

Until the New Year's 30th, Lao Gao had no fever, but because Lao Gao had a fever before, for safety reasons, the three of us still dare not relax. Normally, except for eating and drinking water, we all wear masks, tableware are all separated, and we eat with communal chopsticks, wipe and disinfect all hand contact points in the house. On the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, I saw the residential property sent a friend circle to ask the owners to report Wuhan Personnel Information, we took the initiative to report and register personnel information.

That afternoon, the city CDC came, took the temperature, issued a mask, told home quarantine. January 28, old high fever again, accompanied by diarrhea, vomiting, we rushed to the hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine, and explained the situation in recent days. Doctors filmed CT  , who said there was something wrong with his lungs that was suspected but not confirmed, and recommended isolation before being transferred to Zhongshan's second hospital for treatment under isolation. Lao Gao was quarantined, I am a little flustered, but in front of his son or to show calm, back home, I touched Lao Gao all things have been sterilized again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lao Gao's quarantined hospital, Zhongshan's Second Hospital | south + 

Before going to bed, the son specially orders, requests our room door to be open, has the indisposition each other to look after. The next day I woke up with two pieces of good news from the hospital. One is that both my son and I are fine, but the doctor says we need to talk to a specialist about how to protect ourselves. Another is, under the doctor's good care, the old high fever has subsided. In the home these days, we basically do not go out, eat at home to solve, buy food, take out the garbage and other needs of the property to help.

On January 30, the City Center for Disease Control and Prevention called to say that close contacts of suspected cases should be quarantined and all expenses paid by the government. Let us prepare. Now, I have the bottom of the heart, hanging heart can finally a little bit relaxed, and son packed his bags, together on the ambulance. I didn't realize my first time in an ambulance was like this.

Arriving at the hotel, the staff wore protective clothing and goggles, but they were very nice. The first time by others with alternative vision to treat, although not adapt to, but especially understand. The hotel is very large, the environment is good, my son and I were isolated in a single room and a double room, the hotel staff delivered three meals a day, garbage collection point. Breakfast is Lean Porridge, steamed stuffed Bun, Rice Porridge, fried dough sticks, lunch and dinner, as well as Zhongshan's local Vermicelli, or even ten yuan a catty of Dutch beans, Fried Bacon.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image of Chen Xuan's isolated hotel room | provided by interviewees

Epidemic Prevention Staff is also very responsible, twice a day home temperature measurement, are currently normal. A wandering in the Hubei Province, in this special period, the government can be warm care, very moved. And thousands of miles away, my colleagues are also doing their part for the Wuhan front-line medical staff. Since the closure of 150 bakeries in various districts, they have taken turns spontaneously making as much bread as possible every day and sending it to hospitals in Wuhan. At present, and Wuhan Nine Hospitals, eight hospitals in Wuhan, Hankou Hospital, and 16 other hospitals to communicate good distribution matters, other aid hospitals are also continuing docking.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chen Xuan's colleagues provide free bread to the Wuhan first-line Hospital every day

Today is the sixth day of Laogao's isolation, the fourth day of my isolation with my son. I video-chatted with them in the group in the morning. My Son has reported the situation to the school, reading books and Practicing Guitar Every day, leading a full life, also from the beginning of fatigue, loss of appetite, to now a good appetite, appetite, he also jokingly encouraged me to say: "When I get out of the hospital, you can do a table for me to eat, AH, we have to run exercise together... "
